54.6	James_Ussher	James Ussher	James Ussher (sometimes spelled Usher, 4 January 1581 â€“ 21 March 1656) was Church of Ireland Archbishop of Armagh and Primate of All Ireland between 1625 and 1656. He was a prolific scholar, who most famously published a chronology that purported to establish the time and date of the creation as the night preceding Sunday, 23 October 4004 BC, according to the proleptic Julian calendar.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1c/James_Ussher_by_Sir_Peter_Lely.jpg/220px-James_Ussher_by_Sir_Peter_Lely.jpg
